    • Enum Constant Detail

      • CMDDLM

        public static final CommandName CMDDLM
        The space character as delimiter of command parts in string command representation.

      • CMDUDLM

        public static final CommandName CMDUDLM
        The single quote character (') as delimiter of recipient user list in CMDPRVMSG from over command parts in string command representation.

      • CMDULDLM

        public static final CommandName CMDULDLM
        The delimiter inside recipient user list in CMDPRVMSG in string command representation.

      • CMDEXIT

        public static final CommandName CMDEXIT
        The command to close chat session. Initiated by client or server.

      • CMDENTER

        public static final CommandName CMDENTER
        The command to start chat session. Initiated by client, processed by server. Payload must contain user name.

      • CMDUSRLST

        public static final CommandName CMDUSRLST
        The command to update user list on client View. Payload is a string of the user names with CMDDLM as delimiter. Initiated by server, processed by client.

      • CMDPRVMSG

        public static final CommandName CMDPRVMSG
        The command to send private chat messages. Initiated by client, processed by server. Payload list of message recipients.

      • CMDMSG

        public static final CommandName CMDMSG
        The command to send chat messages. Initiated by client, processed by server. Message contain chat message, payload is empty.

      • CMDERR

        public static final CommandName CMDERR
        The error command, using if something going wrong. Example client or server receive unknown command. Initiated by client or server, message contains error message.

      • CMDHLP

        public static final CommandName CMDHLP
        The command to display help for supported commands. Initiated by client or server.

      • CMDOK

        public static final CommandName CMDOK
        The command to approve client chat session establishing. Initiated by server, processed by client. Payload is a approved command name.
